### Ionic Framework Version

v7.x

### Current Behavior

At initiating IonModal with IonDatetime component with specific configuration, IonDatetime is not presented with wheels, but as calendar. On second click it is presented as wheel picker. Also, there is an error in the console. 
```
template.html:11 ERROR TypeError: Cannot redefine property: cancelText
    at Function.defineProperty (<anonymous>)
    at ionic-angular-standalone.mjs:210:16
    at Array.forEach (<anonymous>)
    at proxyInputs (ionic-angular-standalone.mjs:209:12)
    at IonDatetime.ngOnInit (ionic-angular-standalone.mjs:2202:9)
    at callHookInternal (core.mjs:4024:14)
    at callHook (core.mjs:4051:13)
    at callHooks (core.mjs:4006:17)
    at executeInitAndCheckHooks (core.mjs:3956:9)
    at refreshView (core.mjs:13513:21)
```
[iondatetime-error-standalone.webm](https://github.com/ionic-team/ionic-framework/assets/80419964/b052a419-7f05-46cc-8569-ac230144ac60)

I have followed steps from tutorial on how to use Ionic Angular standalone with NgModules based app.

### Expected Behavior

The IonDatetime standalone component should always have wheels and not have errored.

### Steps to Reproduce

**1. Create FormDate component**
